# dCloud prototype

A prototype reimagining of Cisco **dCloud** (Cisco's sales demonstration platform) — a "complete step-change", explicitly **not a reskin** of today's dCloud. The current dCloud is the **anti-pattern**: a flat, dense, text-heavy card-list / accordion-sidebar with poor raw search and no journey between demos. Diverge from it.

## Source of truth

`context.md` is the source of truth for *what* to build. When the brief and the code disagree, surface the conflict rather than silently picking one. This file distills the durable constraints plus the conventions established in code.

## Commands

```bash
npm run dev        # Vite dev server on :5173
npm run build      # tsc -b (typecheck) then vite build → dist/
npm run typecheck  # tsc -b --noEmit, no build output
npm run preview    # serve the production build
```

## Stack & conventions

**React 19 + Vite 6 + TypeScript + React Router 7.**

- **Styling: custom CSS + design tokens** (no CSS framework). All colours/spacing/type/radii live as CSS variables in `src/styles/tokens.css` — consume them, never hard-code. Component styles are **CSS Modules** (`Foo.module.css`) co-located with the component. Global resets and the `.gradient-text` helper are in `src/styles/global.css`.
- **Imports** use the `@/` alias for `src/` (configured in `vite.config.ts` and `tsconfig.app.json`).
- **Layout:** pages in `src/pages/<Name>/`, reusable components in `src/components/<Name>/`, non-UI logic in `src/lib/`, file-based seed data in `src/data/`.
- **Auth/session** is centralised in `src/lib/auth.ts`: a simulated SSO that reads/writes the current `User` to `localStorage` under `dcloud.user`. `RequireAuth` (`src/components/RequireAuth.tsx`) gates every route except the public landing.

## Hard constraints (do not violate)

- **No backend.** Everything is client-side. Persist all state in **`localStorage`**.
- **File-based test data.** Seed/demo content lives in files in the repo (`src/data/catalog.ts`), not a database or API.
- **History and scoring are per-user** and must be obvious in the UI.

## UX north-star

**Modern, dark, spacious.** Visual reference is **Cisco Cloud Control** (dark, centred "Hi, <Name>", gradient glow, pill chips, colourful viz on dark). **Keep pages clean — do not pile many different things onto one page.**

## Core domain model

Strict connectivity hierarchy — content is organised around GTM, never as one flat list:

```
GTM Motions          (top level; editable)
  Solution Spaces    (the marquee idea; each has a UNIQUE background)
    Demos & Labs     (Solution · Deep-Dive · Guided · Lab)
```

- Everything connects **upstream**; a demo should **never be orphaned**.
- Connections are **manual** (Admin UI later), not auto-derived from tags.

## Terminology (revises context.md)

- The UI uses **Solution Spaces**, *not* "Zones".
- **My Spaces** = a seller's own custom, customer-scoped Spaces, built from Solution Spaces; publishable as a **dCloud eXpo** (branded, time-bound, shareable, joinable — concept from Cisco's real eXpo; do NOT copy the old eXpo UI).
- **Gamification is deliberately very soft** — kept off the hub; full status ladder lives on the Profile page.

